    <summary>Demonstrates how to use physics simulation in Duality.</summary>
    <description>This package contains a testbed for RigidBody physics simulation, showing various aspects of their configuration and interaction.</description>
    <tags>Duality Sample Plugin Physics</tags>
    <releaseNotes>Physics Sample: Collision Filters, Physics Sample: Force / Impulse / Velocity, Physics Sample API Update
#ADD: Added a physics sample for collision filtering via code.
#ADD: Added a physics sample for applying forces, impulses and velocities.
#CHANGE: Updated physics sample code to newer, non-obsolete RigidBody API.
#ADD: Added a physics sample for physics rect queries.
#ADD: Added a physics sample for raycasts.
#ADD: Added a physics sample for collision handling.
#FIX: Fixed the description text of the sensor physics sample that previously used the one from the tower sample.
#ADD: Added a physics sample for sensor shapes.
#CHANGE: Removed unnecessary floor objects from physics samples.
#ADD: Added a physics sample for lots of stacked objects / tower stability.
#ADD: Added a physics sample for collision groups.</releaseNotes>
